        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "\n\n\t\t\t\t\t \n\n                 \t\n\n\n\t ┬½ All Events\n\n\t\n\tThis event has passed.\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\tLobby Exhibition: Indigenous Art Show\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\tJune 3, 2026 @ 10:00 am - July 1, 2026 @ 2:00 pm\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\nSweetgrass Arts and Music Society Presents: Indigenous Art Show at ArtSpring\nJoin us at ArtSpring for a vibrant celebration of Indigenous creativity, culture, and community. This special exhibition brings together a diverse mix of Indigenous artists, showcasing works that reflect story, land, tradition, and contemporary expression.\nAlongside the main show, we are hoping to include a dedicated childrenŌĆÖs exhibitŌĆöhighlighting young voices and emerging talent, and creating space for the next generation of artists to share their vision.\nThis gathering is more than an art showŌĆöit is a place to connect, learn, and celebrate the richness of Indigenous art across generations.\nAll are welcome.\nArtists:\nRose Spahan ŌĆō Rose Spahan is a Coast Salish artist known for her work connected to Indigenous culture and Northwest Coast artistic traditions. Her art often reflects themes of ancestry, spirituality, nature, and community, drawing from Salish design elements and storytelling practices.\nQuentin Harris ŌĆō Quentin Harris has been practicing West Coast Native Art for over thirty years. Born Secwepemc, yet raised coastal, has resulted in Quentin finding his own style. He aspires to intersect First Nations art and culture with positive values and truth.\nPatricia Rose Williams ŌĆō Born on Treaty Six territory in Alberta, Patricia Rose Williams now lives on Salt Spring Island, the shared, traditional, unceded territories of the Coast Salish Peoples, including the HulŌĆÖqumiŌĆÖnum and Sencoten speaking peoples. Patricia Rose Williams is a M├®tis artist whose work explores themes of ancestral memory, cultural identity, land-based relationships, and resilience. Working primarily in fused glass, textiles, botanical printing, painting and photography, she blends traditional M├®tis material arts with contemporary techniques, creating layered, symbolic works that honor Wahkohtowin ŌĆō the interconnectedness and reciprocity of all life.\nSherry Leigh Williams ŌĆō Sherry Leigh Williams is a contemporary M├®tis artist, musician, and cultural leader whose work bridges ancestral memory, beadwork tradition, and contemporary painting. Drawing on her Red River M├®tis and Papaschase lineage, she creates richly layered works that honour story, land, kinship, and survival.\n\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\n\n\n\n\t Details \n\t\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\tStart:\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t June 3, 2026 @ 10:00 am \n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\tEnd:\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t July 1, 2026 @ 2:00 pm \n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\tEvent Categories: ASP-slider, Lobby Exhibits, Rental\n\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tWebsite:\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t https://www.sweetgrassartsandmusicofsaltspringisland.com \n\t\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\n\n\n\tOrganizer\n\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\tSweetgrass Arts & Music\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\n\n\t\n\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\n\n\t Venue \n\t\n\t\t\t\t ArtSpring ŌĆō Lobby \n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n100 Jackson Avenue\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\tSalt Spring Island,\n\n\tBC\n\n\tV8K 2V8\n\n\tCanada\n\n\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t+ Google Map\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\tPhone\n\t\t\t\t\t 250.537.2102 \n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\n\n\n\t\n\n\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\n\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\tAdd to calendar\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\n\t\tGoogle Calendar\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\n\t\tiCalendar\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\n\t\tOutlook 365\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t