    "http://schema.org/description": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "&lt;p&gt;Open Daily 10am-4pm and before theatre performances. In HamletŌĆÖs &quot;To Be or Not To Be&quot; soliloquy he contemplates life and death, using ŌĆ£Undiscovered Country&quot; as a metaphor for the unknown [&hellip;]&lt;/p&gt;\\n"
